social: Will Petroglyphs of Ratnagiri, dated to around 10,000 BCE, change the date of the Kurukshetra War? Petroglyphs are prehistoric drawings or carvings on rock. Some are about 25,000 years old, and others are dated to 10,000-3000 BCE. They could be Mesolithic or Neolithic. Petroglyphs have been found all over the world, except for Antarctica. The highest concentrations are in Africa, Scandinavia, and Siberia. Many petroglyphs date back to around 10,000 to 12,000 years ago, around the Neolithic and late Upper Paleolithic boundary. Geoglyphs are a type of art that has existed since the Palaeolithic era and represent the transition of human culture from the early Stone Age to the Early Historic Period.  Some geoglyphs were built in two main periods, one in the Late Neolithic about 6,500 BCE and one about 3400 BCE during the Early Bronze Age. Geoglyphs and petroglyphs are carvings made of stone tools.  No metallic tools are required to create geoglyphs or petroglyphs. Thus, they have been there since the Palaeolithic era. Kurukshetra War uses technologies like war chariots, iron arrows, bronze weapons, war elephants, etc. that involve the use of Bronze (ayas) and Iron (krishna-ayas). It occurred when the Bronze Age transitioned into the Iron Age in around 2000-1700 BCE. In India, the Bronze Age started in 3300 BCE, and the Iron Age started in 2000 BCE. Manu is the oldest figure mentioned in the Vedic civilization. There are not enough generations between Manu and Parikshit, (born a year after the Kurukshetra War). The lineage from Pariksit to Manu, with its 50 or so generations, extends up to 4000 BCE only. Adding maximum gaps between generations and adding allowances for missing kings, the lineage from Parikshit to Manu reaches only up to around 8000 BCE. Vedic civilization is a product of settlements in Sarasvati, which is far away in the north of Ratnagiri in Maharashtra. It was a Bronze Age civilization, with plenty of references to Bronze (Ayas). Thus, what we see in Ratnagiri is not Vedic civilization either. It is just another civilization of Bharata, which happened to be older than the Vedic civilization. There are numerous civilizations in Bharata which are older than the Vedic civilization.

Only science, use of satellite maps, and powerful computers, that our forecasts have helped us know what will happen tomorrow.
